!Callout macros and class attribute

Callout macro has a `class` attribute lets pass extra css classes to customize it.  Any CSS relevant classes can be used, but mostly customized classes are used for this purpose. In Shiraz 2.0+ these classes are courtesy from Bootstrap and can be found in Shiraz `demo/bootstrap-classes`.

!! Examples i
See below examples. Few classes like text color, element width, and text styling are used here!

```
<<callout note src:"text-primary" class:"text-primary">>
<<callout quote src:"text-secondary" class:"text-secondary">>
<<callout question src:"text-success" class:"text-success">>
<<callout todo src:"text-info" class:"text-info">>
<<callout error src:"text-danger" class:"text-danger">>
<<callout warning src:"text-warning" class:"text-warning">>
<<callout tip src:"text-info" class:"text-info">>
```
